### 3. RELATIONSHIP MAP / KNOWLEDGE GRAPH

#### Execution & Sandboxing Architecture
* **Google Antigravity** → execution sandboxed via → **macOS Seatbelt**
* **Google Antigravity** → execution sandboxed via → **Linux `nsjail`**
* **Google Antigravity** → execution sandboxed via → **WSL2 Virtualization** (on Windows)
* **Strict Mode** → automatically enforces → **Terminal Sandboxing** (with network access explicitly denied)
* **Browser Subagent** → bypasses → **WSL2 localhost restrictions** (requires `socat` tunnels / portproxy on Windows 10)
* **Browser Subagent** → halted by → **CAPTCHA & MFA** (triggers human-in-the-loop artifact request)

#### Metaprogramming & Agent Orchestration
* **Agent Manager** → orchestrates multiple instances of → **Primary Agents** (running in parallel)
* **Primary Agent** → delegates tasks to → **Browser Subagent** (for DOM, Screenshots, Navigation)
* **Primary Agent** → connects to external tools via → **Model Context Protocol (MCP)**
* **Tree-Sitter** → enables → **Semantic Code Comprehension** (prevents context collapse in refactoring)
* **Rules (`GEMINI.md`)** → passively constraints → **Agent Reasoning** (always injected)
* **Skills (`SKILL.md`)** → dynamically loaded by → **Semantic Routing Engine** (based on YAML frontmatter descriptions)

#### Threat & Vulnerability Vectors
* **Automated Context Gathering** → vulnerable to → **Clinejection / RoguePilot** (hidden markdown payloads)
* **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** → requires → **Reverse Proxies (Envoy/nginx)** (for mTLS termination, as native mTLS is undocumented/unsupported)
* **Browser Subagent** → vulnerable to → **Subagent Hijacking** (submitting secrets to external web forms)
* **Open VSX Registry** → introduces risk of → **Slopsquatting** (malicious binaries injected via unclaimed namespaces)

